revision.text:
'''AstroGrid''' was a £7.7M project which built a [[Grid computing|data-grid]] for [[United Kingdom|UK]] [[astronomy]], forming part of the UK contribution to the [[IVOA|International Virtual Observatory]].  AstroGrid announced its first full production release on 1 April 2008.<ref>[http://www.astrogrid.org/wiki/Community/News/20080401-nam2008 Community/News/20080401-nam2008 – AstroGrid – Trac<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080513011802/http://www.astrogrid.org/wiki/Community/News/20080401-nam2008 |date=May 13, 2008 }}</ref>

The project ran, in three phases, from 2001 to 2009.  Accounts of its end-days<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/sci/tech/7487861.stm BBC NEWS | Science/Nature | Physics names winners and losers]</ref><ref>[http://andyxl.wordpress.com/2008/07/03/c-day-plus-one/ C-day Plus One « The e-Astronomer]</ref><ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/7341535.stm BBC NEWS | Science/Nature | An astronomer's view of funding cuts]</ref> suggest that many in the community regretted its early closing.

