'''De Lalande''' is a multiring [[impact crater]] on [[Venus]].<ref name=usgs>{{cite web|title=de Lalande|url=http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/1441|publisher=[[U.S. Geological Survey]]|accessdate=19 November 2012}}</ref> It has a diameter of {{convert|21.6|km|mi|abbr=on}} and wall width of {{convert|5.6|km|mi|abbr=on}}.<ref name=usra>{{cite web|title=de Lalande|url=http://www.lpi.usra.edu/resources/vc/vcinfo/?refnum=298|publisher=USRA|accessdate=19 November 2012}}</ref> The crater has an outer rim but no peak and is in close proximity to the volcano [[Gula Mons]].<ref name=nasa>{{cite web|last=Weitz|first=Catherine E.|title=Chapter 7. Impact Craters|url=https://history.nasa.gov/JPL-93-24/ch7.htm|publisher=[[NASA]]|accessdate=19 November 2012}}</ref>

==Namesake==
[[File:Jerome de Lalande AGE V01 1798.jpg|thumb|French astronomer Jérôme Lalande]]
The de Lalande crater is named after the French astronomer [[Marie-Jeanne de Lalande]] (1768-1832),<ref>{{Gpn|1441|Lalande}}</ref> illegitimate daughter of astronomer [[Joseph Jerome de Lalande]] (1732-1807).

