==Europe== Europe is sometimes considered to be a large peninsula extending off [[Eurasia]].<ref name="Peninsula">{{cite web |editor=National Geographic |title= Peninsula |year=1996 |url= http://education.nationalgeographic.com/education/encyclopedia/peninsula/?ar_a=1|accessdate=18 January 2015}}</ref> As such, it is one of the largest peninsulas in the world and the only one to have the status as a full continent, largely as a matter of convention rather than science. It is composed of many smaller peninsulas, the four main component peninsulas being the [[Iberian Peninsula|Iberian]], [[Scandinavian Peninsula|Scandinavian]], [[Italian Peninsula|Italian]], and [[Balkan Peninsula|Balkan]] peninsulas.
=== Balkan Peninsula === The [[Balkans]] is a peninsula including Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Croatia, Greece, Kosovo, [[Macedonia (country)|Macedonia]], Montenegro, Romania, Serbia, Slovenia and the [[East Thrace|European part]] of Turkey.
