{{Infobox scientist |name = Paul Breslin |image = |image_size = 300px |caption = |birth_date = |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |residence = [[Pennsylvania]] |citizenship = |nationality = |ethnicity = |fields = [[psychology|psychologist]], [[Genetics|Geneticist]] |workplaces = [[Monell Chemical Senses Center]], [[Rutgers University]] |alma_mater = [[University of Pennsylvania]] |doctoral_advisor = |academic_advisors = |doctoral_students = |notable_students = |known_for = Work with human oral perception and flies |author_abbrev_bot = |author_abbrev_zoo = |influences = |influenced = |awards = |religion = |signature = |footnotes = }}
'''Dr. Paul Breslin''' is a [[geneticist]] and [[biologist]].
He is most notable for his work in taste perception and oral irritation,<ref>{{Citation | first = Paul | last = Breslin | author-link = | first2 = Alan | last2 = Spector | author2-link = | editor-last = | editor-first = | editor2-last = | editor2-first = | contribution = | contribution-url = | title = A Quantitative Comparison of Taste Reactivity Behaviors to Sucrose Before and After Lithium Chloride Pairings: A Unidimensional Account of Palatability | year = 1992 | pages = | place = Philadelphia | publisher = Behavioral Neuroscience | url = http://www.sciencedirect.com/science?_ob=ArticleURL&_udi=B6WY4-46V0BFG-1K&_user=10&_coverDate=10%2F31%2F1992&_alid=773747780&_rdoc=21&_fmt=high&_orig=search&_cdi=7176&_sort=d&_docanchor=&view=c&_ct=23&_acct=C000050221&_version=1&_urlVersion=0&_userid=10&md5=64c4461bb5225a1aa785b22902a90c01 | doi = | id = }}</ref> in humans as well as in ''[[Drosophila melanogaster]]'', the common fruit fly.
He is a Member at the [[Monell Chemical Senses Center]] and acts as Director of the [http://www.monell.org/education_training/science_apprenticeship_program/program_overview Science Apprenticeship Program]. He is a Professor in the [http://nutrition.rutgers.edu/ Department of Nutritional Sciences] at [[Rutgers]], the State University of New Jersey.
